history.content: If the 61BL instructors wanted you for that role, we could set up a section of CS197 for you to receive units.   In summer session, each unit would carry on expectation of 6 hours/week of commitment. (It would be 3 hours in Fall or Spring when the semester is basically twice as long.)

I plan on taking CS61C (4 units) during the summer and no other courses, but to qualify for financial aid I need to have a minimum of 6 units.

 

Does anyone know if I can get the additional 2 units by lab assisting for CS 61B during the summer and would those units count toward the minimum? How many hours of commitment is required per unit?
history.subject: Can I get units for lab assisting/reader?
